//! Generated Code Module
//!
//! This module contains all code generated by `ggen sync` from RDF ontologies.
//!
//! ## Structure
//!
//! The generated code follows Domain-Driven Design (DDD) principles:
//!
//! - **domain/** - Core domain model
//!   - **entities/** - Objects with identity and lifecycle
//!   - **value_objects/** - Immutable objects without identity
//!   - **aggregates/** - Consistency boundaries with root entities
//!   - **events/** - Domain events for state changes
//!   - **services/** - Stateless domain operations
//! - **commands/** - CQRS command handlers
//! - **queries/** - CQRS query handlers
//! - **repositories/** - Data access abstractions
//!
//! ## Frozen Sections
//!
//! Generated files support frozen sections to preserve custom code during regeneration:
//!
//! ```rust,ignore
//! // === ggen:frozen:start:custom_validation ===
//! // Your custom validation logic here - preserved during regeneration
//! fn custom_validate(&self) -> bool {
//!     // Custom implementation
//!     true
//! }
//! // === ggen:frozen:end:custom_validation ===
//! ```
//!
//! Frozen section markers:
//! - `// === ggen:frozen:start:<section_name> ===` - Begin frozen section
//! - `// === ggen:frozen:end:<section_name> ===` - End frozen section
//!
//! ## Integration with Hand-Written Code
//!
//! Generated code is designed to be extended by hand-written code in `src/domain/`:
//!
//! 1. **Trait Implementation**: Implement generated traits in your domain types
//! 2. **Extension Traits**: Add methods via extension traits
//! 3. **Composition**: Wrap generated types with domain-specific behavior
//!
//! Example:
//! ```rust,ignore
//! use crate::generated::domain::entities::Workbook;
//!
//! // Extension trait for custom behavior
//! pub trait WorkbookExt {
//!     fn calculate_complexity(&self) -> u32;
//! }
//!
//! impl WorkbookExt for Workbook {
//!     fn calculate_complexity(&self) -> u32 {
//!         // Custom implementation
//!         0
//!     }
//! }
//! ```
//!
//! ## Regeneration
//!
//! To regenerate code: `ggen sync`
//!
//! Options:
//! - `ggen sync --dry_run true` - Preview changes without writing
//! - `ggen sync --force true` - Force regeneration (respects frozen sections)
//! - `ggen sync --audit true` - Generate with audit trail

